<c74object name='sp.convolver~' category='' module='SP-Tools'>
    <digest>Zero-latency convolution
</digest>
    <description>Zero-latency convolution.
</description>
    <discussion><h4><openfilelink filename="SP-Tools Overview.maxpat">Open the Overview Patch</openfilelink></h4>
The <o>sp.convolver~</o> object is a zero-latency convolution abstraction powered by the HIRT <o>multiconvolve~</o> object. You can point it to an external IR (mono or stereo) or read/load an IR into its internal <o>buffer~</o>.
</discussion>

	<metadatalist>
		<metadata name='author'>Rodrigo Constanzo, Flucoma Project</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Machine Learning</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Audio Analysis</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Onset Detection</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Corpus Playback</metadata>
	</metadatalist>

    <!-- INLETS -->
    <inletlist>
        <inlet id='0' type='signal'>
            <digest>Audio input
</digest>
            <description>Audio input.
</description>
        </inlet>
    </inletlist>
    <!-- INLETS -->

    <!-- OUTLETS -->
    <outletlist>
        <outlet id='0' type='signal'>
            <digest>Audio output (L)
</digest>
            <description>Audio output (left).
</description>
        </outlet>
        <outlet id='1' type='signal'>
            <digest>Audio output (R)
</digest>
            <description>Audio outout (right).
</description>
        </outlet>
    </outletlist>
    <!-- OUTLETS -->

    <!-- ARGUMENTS -->
    <objarglist>
        <objarg name='default' optional='1' type='symbol'>
            <digest>IR to load by default
</digest>
            <description>IR file to load by default.
</description>
        </objarg>
    </objarglist>
    <!-- ARGUMENTS -->

    <!--MESSAGES-->
    <methodlist>
    <method name='load'>
        <arglist>
        </arglist>
        <digest>Load an IR file
</digest>
        <description>Opens file dialog to select an impulse response file.
</description>
    </method>
    <method name='read'>
        <arglist>
        </arglist>
        <digest>Read an IR file
</digest>
        <description>Reads an impulse response file directly from a relative or absolute path.
</description>
    </method>
    <method name='set'>
        <arglist>
        </arglist>
        <digest>Sets the <o>buffer~</o> with an IR
</digest>
        <description>Sets the <o>buffer~</o> with an impulse response file.
</description>
    </method>
	</methodlist>
